      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "The Goblin's Gambit! It's an old goblin proverb that means outsmarting your opponents by taking a calculated risk. In this case, it's about finding the best route to Singapore despite the airline's cancellation. Think of it like a goblin's clever trick to get out of a tight spot.\n\nNow, let's get down to business. I've got some route suggestions for you:\n\n1. Emirates: You can fly from Heathrow to Dubai, then connect to Singapore. This route takes around 12 hours, depending on the layover time.\n2. Qatar Airways: Another option is to fly from Heathrow to Doha, then connect to Singapore. This route takes around 13 hours, with a layover time of around 2 hours.\n3. Thai Airways: You can fly from Heathrow to Bangkok, then connect to Singapore. This route takes around 14 hours, with a layover time of around 2 hours.\n\nWhen it comes to prioritizing which route to book, consider the following factors:\n\n* Layover time: Look for routes with shorter layover times to minimize your overall travel time.\n* Flight duration: Choose the route with the shortest flight duration to get to Singapore as quickly as possible.",
